MatchedObjectDescriptor.QualificationSummary:
Your resume must demonstrate at least one year of specialized experience at or equivalent to the GS-06 grade level or pay band in the Federal service or equivalent experience in the private or public sector applying a knowledge and application of transportation regulations, policies, methods, procedures and practices to perform a wide variety of transportation support assignments. Examples of specialized experience include: 1) Securing carriers to arrange for pickup, delivery, and storage of shipments; identify the mode or combination of modes, types of special equipment, and services required for shipments;
2) Advising customers of inadequacies or inaccuracies in shipping requests and related documentation;
3) Ensuring proper handling, documentation and accounting for shipping requirements of cargo freight shipments to include proper record management;
4) Reviewing documentation and conducts research on any discrepancies.. Additional qualification information can be found from the following Office of Personnel Management website:
https://www.opm.gov/policy-data-oversight/classification-qualifications/general-schedule-qualification-standards/#url=List-by-Occupational-Series Experience refers to paid and unpaid experience, including volunteer work done through National Service programs (e.g., professional, philanthropic, religious, spiritual, community, student, social). Volunteer work helps build critical competencies, knowledge, and skills and can provide valuable training and experience that translates directly to paid employment.
